Lloyd A. Carney: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 1:06 PM ET
Communications Equipment

Company Overview of Brocade Communications Systems, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Lloyd A. Carney  Chief Executive Officer and Director, Brocade Communications Systems, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships55$6,092,213As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Lloyd A. Carney has been the Chief Executive Officer of Brocade Communications Systems, Inc., since January 14, 2013. Mr. Carney served as the Chief Executive Officer of Xsigo Systems, Inc. since January 2008 until July 2012. He served as an Advisor of Technicolor SA. He served as General Manager of Netcool Products, IBM. He was responsible for integrating Micromuse Netcool solutions into IBM Tivoli Portfolio. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman ... of Micromuse, Inc. since July 28, 2003 until 2006. Mr. Carney joined Bay Networks, Inc. in 1990 and served as its Executive Vice President of Operations and General Manager of Enterprise Business Group since January 1997. He joined Juniper Networks, Inc. in January 2002 and served as its Executive Vice President of Operations since January 2002 and also served as its Chief Operations Officer, where he oversaw a broad range of business operations including the sales, marketing, engineering, manufacturing and customer service organizations. From May 2001 to September 2001, he served as the President of the Core IP Division of Nortel Networks. From March 2000 to May 2001, he served as the President of the Wireless Internet Division of Nortel Networks Corporation. From June 1997 to March 2000, he served as President of the Enterprise Data Division of Nortel Networks. Prior to that, Mr. Carney served as Vice President of Worldwide Customer Service of Nortel Networks Inc. A twenty-year veteran of the networking industry, he has held managerial and engineering roles at Prime Computer, Proteon and Radio Corporation of America (RCA). He has been Independent Director at Visa Inc. since June 11, 2015. He has been a Director of Brocade Communications Systems, Inc. since February 2013. He served as a Director at Technicolor SA since June 17, 2010. He served as a Director of Cypress Semiconductor Corporation from June 23, 2005 to May 9, 2014. He served as a Director at Micromuse, Inc. since July 29, 2003 and BigBand Networks, Inc., from April 18, 2006 to June 2008. He served as Director of Xsigo Systems, Inc. from January 2008 to July 2012. He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering Technology from Wentworth Institute and a Master of Science degree in Applied Business Management from Lesley College, Cambridge, Massachusetts.Read Full Background




